Yes. Anything that can help give a little bit of the Classic XP look, <br />can go a long way to the feel of it.<br /><br />Different text size in each column. -9 /-10<br />Different font semiboldness levels<br />Blue colors on second column text and arrows<br /><br />If everyone used default XP settings, one size icons could be embedded into the skin, <br />with text padding to accommodate the icons space. That is not gonna happen. <br />We are all different, and use the start menu a thousand different ways.<br /><br />Looking good though. Keep going Splitwirez, and others.<br />Getting closer.<br /><br />Addition.<br />If you are going to use the icon shutdown button, <br />I screwed up on the font size.<br />I put it as -10. The original might be -9 or even-8.<br />If font size is changed, its text padding height,<br />would have to increase to get the hover select color, proper height again.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Mon Aug 15, 2016 5:11 pm</p><hr />
